Given the explicit enjoyment of listening to CDs and the extra value I place on cohesive album production and full-album listening, I choose Boston. Its consistent, high-fidelity production and unified album experience better match my CD-enthusiast priorities. I reject Tom Petty & The Heartbreakers: Greatest Hits not because it isn’t excellent — it is — but because its compilation nature makes it less aligned with my preference for experiencing an album as a cohesive, sonically unified work on CD.

