- CD 1 (1959 modal jazz landmark) has qualities I admire in isolation—warm tape saturation, intimate midrange and uncompressed dynamics—but it diverges from my core priorities: it’s piano‑forward (not guitar/groove‑forward), features airy room imaging and sparse interplay that emphasize room and immersion rather than hook focus, and it represents whole‑disc, uncompressed, live interplay rather than concise, front‑loaded pop singles. The roomy, live-take aesthetic risks pushing any vocals or hooks back and sacrificing the immediate, stacked‑harmony, hook‑first presentation I prefer.
